&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
(Posted in various taverns across Norrath.  Some copies have been seen blown about the Plane of Knowledge)<br>
<br>
“Races of Norrath, Xsasx greets you.  I am newly hatched…come…to this world.  If upon your quests you see the need to remove obstacles of the fleshly kind, I would be most willing to assist you with this obstacle.  Please leave a message with the owner of this fine establishment on how I may contact you.”<br>
<br>
I must learn the other tongues of this land.  It is stupidity.  The only thing I need to learn can be found in a fresh corpse.  However, if I am to accomplish my endeavor, I must actually interact with these other inferior races.  Where am I going to find a foul elf who will be willing teach me?  It will be difficult enough to find an elf below the surface of this world to teach me their tongue, but how to even approach a wood elf or a high elf?  <br>
<br>
To make matters even worse, I am commanded to not kill or torture the one who teaches me!  I had hoped to experiment with cutting open their skulls to figure out how the brain tissue worked as they spoke.  That hope is now lost.  Cursed teacher.<br>
<br>
Most of my race that knows these languages do not visit our home very often.  Maybe soon I will be able to grab a few moments of their time to at least learn some phrases to get me started.<br>
<br>
I tire of killing these beetles and scorpions.  I look forward to the day when I will be able to sneak into that gnome city and bring terror into their dreams.<br>
<br>
Upon waking this morning, a brilliant idea has occurred to me.  I have been instructed to not kill the one who teaches me a language.  However, I have not been told that someone else can do the deed for me.  It is not the ideal situation, but my options are greatly increased now to find a victim.<br>
<br>
Curses upon all that stand against me.  My teacher has learned of my plan.  I fear I was not careful enough in my last meeting with a fellow necromancer.  I have not seen her since.  <br>
<br>
4 seasons of death research<br>
Xsasx<br>
<br>
<br>
